  "texts": [
    "The only global equilibria (43) compatible with the boundary conditions (61) are the Beta distributions h ∞ (w) having both exponents nonnegative (consensus formation inside the population).",
    "This implies in particular that the constants τ q are in fact nonnegative.",
    "Moreover, they are also equi-bounded by λ p (ω p + ε) 2 + λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) -σ 2 p -σ 2 ℓ, for any q ∈ [2, +∞).",
    "Therefore, in the limit q → +∞ we infer the regularity h(t, ⋅) ∈ L ∞ (I) for any t > 0, specifically∥h(t, ⋅)∥ L ∞ (I) ≤ η ∞ e τ∞t ∀t > 0, with η ∞ = ∥h in ∥ L ∞ (I) and τ ∞ = (σ 2 p + σ 2 ℓ) ( λp(ωp+ε) 2 +λ ℓ (ω ℓ +ε) σ 2 p +σ 2 ℓ -1), provided that h in ∈ L ∞ (I).We highlight that Lemma 1 does not imply the uniform-in-time regularity h ∈ L ∞ (R +, L q (I)) for q ≥ 2, assumed in Theorem 2.",
    "Nonetheless, it is still possible to prove that h(t, w) converges toward h ∞ (w) as long as0 ≤ q -1 q (λ p (ω p + ε) 2 + λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) -σ 2 p -σ 2 ℓ) = τ q < τ = λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε),(63)by adapting the proof of Theorem 2, at the instances where the quantity ∥h∥ L ∞ (R+,L q (I)) is used to estimate the time derivative of the relative entropy H(h|h eq)(t)."
